{"data":{"post":{"id":"44c9ae4c-13b5-5345-9c4f-cc471a069645","html":"<p>The Awards for design, creativity and innovation on the internet, aka <a href=\"http://www.awwwards.com\">AWWWARDS</a>, have published the <a href=\"http://www.awwwards.com/annual-awards-2015/\">list of nominated projects for 2015</a>. These awards, together with <a href=\"http://www.thefwa.com/\">theFWA</a>, are the maximum awards given in the Internet. You can call them the Oscars and Grammys of the Internet.</p>\n<p>Anyway, <strong>I have a favourite</strong> and you probably have seen it before. It’s called <a href=\"http://species-in-pieces.com/\">Species in Pieces</a>. A beautiful CSS-based interactive exhibition by <a href=\"http://www.bryanjamesdesign.co.uk/\">Bryan James</a>.</p>\n<p>It’s a remarkable project with a technical difficulty beyond what normal people can imagine, as all the animals have been <strong>hand crafted manually and purely with CSS</strong>. I can see this type of work being recognised in future generations as an example of creative innovation.</p>\n<p>Best of luck with that award!</p>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/dba963dc6ad1297fc73038f12cec1c12/5c252/species-in-pieces-mosaic.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 1200px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 52.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"species in pieces mosaic\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/dba963dc6ad1297fc73038f12cec1c12/5c252/species-in-pieces-mosaic.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/dba963dc6ad1297fc73038f12cec1c12/14964/species-in-pieces-mosaic.png 500w,\n/static/dba963dc6ad1297fc73038f12cec1c12/dd7c9/species-in-pieces-mosaic.png 1000w,\n/static/dba963dc6ad1297fc73038f12cec1c12/5c252/species-in-pieces-mosaic.png 1200w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>","fields":{"slug":"/site-of-the-year-2015/","prefix":"10 January 2016"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Site of the year 2015","category":"work","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"resize":{"src":"/static/79fa90c9d67a932797a92367a039e3f2/73b7f/species-in-pieces.jpg"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/site-of-the-year-2015/","prev":{"id":"fdcbee90-fb6f-5357-bd33-80476f9179ed","fields":{"slug":"/the-best-codepens-of-2015/","prefix":"9 January 2016","source":"posts"},"frontmatter":{"title":"The best codepens of 2015","category":"work"}},"next":{"id":"a3f405d6-5b45-5082-a53b-7a7dd04abed0","fields":{"slug":"/javascript-understanding-the-weird-parts/","prefix":"18 January 2016","source":"posts"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Javascript: understanding the weird parts [Part 1]","category":"work"}},"source":"posts"}}